' replace.n7
' ----------

' 'replace(s, sub, rep)' returns a string where all occurrences of sub in s are replaced with rep.
pln replace("the theater theory is weird", "the", "po")

' 'replace(s, sub, rep, n)' works like 'replace(s, sub, rep)' but starts searching at character
' index n and only replaces the first occurence of sub in s with rep.
pln replace("the theater theory is weird", "the", "po", 5)

system "pause"
